Date: Wed 19 Jul 2000
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: PPI Pakistan Press International, Fri 14 Jul 2000 [edited

Widespread cholera epidemic pose life risk
--------------------------------------
Eruption of cholera epidemic has posed serious life risk to people from
Muzaffarabad and adjoining areas. It has claimed life of 3 [children in
Neelum valley and people are rushing to CMH Muzaffarabad for treatment. The
worst affected areas include Pattika, Garhi Dopatta, Hattian Bala,
Chikothi, Kohala, Barar Kot, Punjgran and various villages from Neelum
valley.
